{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_012PfrkjSY9vKKDPeLmBA18A","type":"tool_result","content":"23:// MachineOSBuild describes a build process managed and deployed by the MCO\n26:type MachineOSBuild struct {\n37:\tSpec MachineOSBuildSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n41:\tStatus MachineOSBuildStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n46:// MachineOSBuildList describes all of the Builds on the system\n50:type MachineOSBuildList struct {\n57:\t// items contains a collection of MachineOSBuild resources.\n59:\tItems []MachineOSBuild `json:\"items,omitempty\"`\n62:// MachineOSBuildSpec describes information about a build process primarily populated from a MachineOSConfig object.\n63:type MachineOSBuildSpec struct {\n67:\t// machineOSConfig references the MachineOSConfig resource that this image build extends.\n69:\tMachineOSConfig MachineOSConfigReference `json:\"machineOSConfig\"`\n70:\t// renderedImagePushSpec is set by the Machine Config Operator from the MachineOSConfig object this build is attached to.\n75:\tRenderedImagePushSpec ImageTagFormat `json:\"renderedImagePushSpec\"`\n78:// MachineOSBuildStatus describes the state of a build and other helpful information.\n80:type MachineOSBuildStatus struct {\n94:\tBuilder *MachineOSBuilderReference `json:\"builder,omitempty\"`\n96:\t// After a successful build or when this MachineOSBuild is deleted, these ephemeral objects will be removed.\n104:\t// buildStart is the timestamp corresponding to the build controller initiating the build backend for this MachineOSBuild.\n122:// MachineOSBuilderReference describes which ImageBuilder backend to use for this build\n125:type MachineOSBuilderReference struct {\n146:\tMachineOSBuildPrepared BuildProgress = \"Prepared\"\n148:\tMachineOSBuilding BuildProgress = \"Building\"\n150:\tMachineOSBuildFailed BuildProgress = \"Failed\"\n152:\tMachineOSBuildInterrupted BuildProgress = \"Interrupted\"\n154:\tMachineOSBuildSucceeded BuildProgress = \"Succeeded\"\n205:// M