{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01Cbv937QRhSKjK4ga8dF6dh","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# MCO Architecture - Component Internals\n2\t\n3\t## Binaries\n4\t\n5\tMCO produces 7 binaries from `cmd/`:\n6\t\n7\t| Binary | Deployment | Purpose |\n8\t|--------|-----------|---------|\n9\t| `machine-config-operator` | Deployment | Top-level operator: syncs all sub-components, manages ClusterOperator status |\n10\t| `machine-config-controller` | Deployment | Runs render, template, node, kubelet-config, container-runtime-config, certrotation, drain controllers |\n11\t| `machine-config-daemon` | DaemonSet | Node agent: fetches and applies configs, handles reboot/drain |\n12\t| `machine-config-server` | DaemonSet (masters) | Serves Ignition configs to bootstrapping/joining nodes via HTTPS |\n13\t| `machine-os-builder` | Deployment | Orchestrates OCL builds (MachineOSBuild jobs) |\n14\t| `machine-config-osimagestream` | Job | Generates OSImageStream from release payload |\n15\t| `apiserver-watcher` | DaemonSet | Monitors local apiserver, writes cloud-routes downfiles |\n16\t\n17\t## Controller Details\n18\t\n19\t### Template Controller (`pkg/controller/template/`)\n20\t- **Watches:** ControllerConfig, APIServer, Secrets, ConfigMaps\n21\t- **Produces:** Base MachineConfig objects from Go templates in `/etc/mcc/templates`\n22\t- **Templates organized by role:** `common/`, `master/`, `worker/`\n23\t- Merges IRI (Internal Release Image) secrets into generated configs\n24\t- Template rendering uses Go `text/template` with cluster state as input\n25\t\n26\t### Render Controller (`pkg/controller/render/`)\n27\t- **Watches:** MachineConfig, MachineConfigPool, OSImageStream, ControllerConfig, ContainerRuntimeConfig\n28\t- **Produces:** Rendered (merged) MachineConfig per pool\n29\t- Merge is deterministic: MachineConfigs sorted by name, last-writer-wins for file conflicts\n30\t- Uses content-based hashing for rendered config naming (avoids unnecessary updates)\n31\t- 5-second render delay to batch rapid changes\n32\t\n33\t### Node Controller (`pkg/controller/node/`)\n34\t- **Watches:** MachineConfigPool, MachineConfig, MachineOSConfig, MachineOSBuild, Node\n35\t- **Manages:** Node annotations (desired/current config), drain coordination, MachineConfigNode status\n36\t- Largest controller (~81KB). Orchestrates the full node update lifecycle:\n37\t  1. Detects config drift between desired and current\n38\t  2. Respects `maxUnavailable` for rolling updates\n39\t  3. Coordinates with MCD for drain, apply, reboot\n40\t  4. Updates MachineConfigPool status counters\n41\t\n42\t### Build Controller (`pkg/controller/build/`)\n43\t- **Watches:** MachineOSBuild, MachineOSConfig, Job, MachineConfigPool\n44\t- **Manages:** OCL build lifecycle via Kubernetes Jobs\n45\t- Subdirectories: `buildrequest/` (build job creation), `imagebuilder/` (podman/buildah), `imagepruner/` (cleanup)\n46\t- Creates Jobs that run `podman build` with user-provided Containerfiles\n47\t- Tracks build status through MachineOSBuild conditions\n48\t\n49\t### KubeletConfig Controller (`pkg/controller/kubelet-config/`)\n50\t- **Watches:** KubeletConfig, MachineConfigPool, ClusterOperator\n51\t- Merges upstream KubeletConfiguration into MachineConfig objects\n52\t- Handles feature gate propagation to kubelet config\n53\t- Supports `autoSizingReserved` for automatic resource reservation\n54\t\n55\t### ContainerRuntimeConfig Controller (`pkg/controller/container-runtime-config/`)\n56\t- **Watches:** ContainerRuntimeConfig, MachineConfigPool\n57\t- Generates CRI-O config files (`/etc/crio/crio.conf.d/`), storage config, registries config\n58\t- Large helper surface (~63KB helpers.go) for registry mirror configuration\n59\t\n60\t### Boot Image Controller (`pkg/controller/bootimage/`)\n61\t- **Watches:** MachineSet, ControlPlaneMachineSet, Infrastructure, ClusterVersion\n62\t- Updates cloud provider boot images (AMIs, Azure images, GCP images)\n63\t- Platform-specific logic for AWS, Azure, GCP, vSphere, OpenStack\n64\t- AMI mapping in `ami.go` (228KB of region-to-AMI mappings)\n65\t\n66\t### Other Controllers\n67\t- **CertRotation** (`pkg/controller/certrotation/`): Rotates MCO serving certificates\n68\t- **PinnedImageSet** (`pkg/controller/pinnedimageset/`): Ensures images are pre-pulled to nodes\n69\t- **Drain** (`pkg/controller/drain/`): Coordinates node drain operations\n70\t- **InternalReleaseImage** (`pkg/controller/internalreleaseimage/`): Extracts image refs from release payloads\n71\t\n72\t## Machine Config Daemon (`pkg/daemon/`)\n73\t\n74\tThe node-level agent. Core file `daemon.go` is ~110KB, `update.go` is ~135KB.\n75\t\n76\t**Responsibilities:**\n77\t- Watches node annotations for desired config changes\n78\t- Applies Ignition configs: writes files, creates systemd units, sets kernel arguments\n79\t- Manages OS updates via rpm-ostree (traditional) or bootc (container-native)\n80\t- Decides reboot vs. service-reload based on change type\n81\t- Config drift monitoring (detects unauthorized file changes)\n82\t- Reports progress via MachineConfigNode conditions\n83\t- Pinned image set management (pre-pulling images)\n84\t- On-disk validation of applied configs\n85\t\n86\t**Update decision tree:**\n87\t- File-only changes with no OS change: service reload (CRIO, kubelet)\n88\t- OS image change or kernel args: full node reboot\n89\t- FIPS change: reboot required\n90\t- Extension changes: reboot required\n91\t\n92\t## Machine Config Server (`pkg/server/`)\n93\t\n94\tHTTPS server on master nodes serving Ignition configs to joining nodes.\n95\t\n96\t- `AppendersBuilder` pattern composes config from multiple sources\n97\t- Appenders: KubeConfig, certificates, node annotations\n98\t- Bootstrap mode: serves from filesystem during cluster install\n99\t- Cluster mode: serves from rendered MachineConfigs via API\n100\t\n101\t## Operator Sync (`pkg/operator/`)\n102\t\n103\tTop-level orchestration in `sync.go` (~113KB):\n104\t\n105\t1. Syncs OSImageStream (image references)\n106\t2. Renders and deploys controller, daemon, server components\n107\t3. Manages RBAC, ServiceAccounts, ConfigMaps, Secrets\n108\t4. Reports ClusterOperator status and conditions\n109\t5. Handles upgrades: version skew, feature gate transitions\n110\t\n111\t## Shared Infrastructure\n112\t\n113\t### `pkg/controller/common/`\n114\t- `controller_context.go`: Shared informer factory, client sets, feature gate state\n115\t- `helpers.go` (~56KB): MC manipulation, Ignition utilities, annotation helpers\n116\t- `layered_node_state.go`: State tracking for OCL nodes\n117\t- `metrics.go`: Prometheus metric definitions\n118\t- `featuregates.go`: Feature gate detection and propagation\n119\t\n120\t### `lib/resourceapply/` and `lib/resourceread/`\n121\t- Idempotent resource application (create-or-update pattern)\n122\t- Type-safe resource deserialization from YAML/JSON\n123\t\n124\t## ValidatingAdmissionPolicies\n125\t\n126\tLocated in `manifests/`:\n127\t- `custom-machine-config-pool-selector`: Custom MCPs must inherit from worker\n128\t- `internalreleaseimage-deletion-guard`: Protects InternalReleaseImage from deletion\n129\t- `machineconfigpool-osimagestream-reference`: OSImageStream ref validation\n130\t- `machineconfiguration-guards`: Global MachineConfiguration guards\n131\t- `mcn-guards`: MachineConfigNode guards\n132\t- `osimagestream-deletion-guard`: Protects OSImageStream from deletion\n133\t- `update-bootimages`: Boot image update validation\n134\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_014NA5Hm4ucczaQabTwCT8iW","session_id":"e75a21bc-7faa-413c-8450-02eaf032edac","uuid":"54ef25a5-7c5e-4d0f-b65a-f89f15cc4ab1","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:07:57.463Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Search for MachineOSConfig and on-cluster layering docs"}
