{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_014NA5Hm4ucczaQabTwCT8iW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a comprehensive picture of MachineOSConfig and on-cluster layering from across the repo. Here is the full report.\n\n---\n\n## MachineOSConfig and On-Cluster Layering (OCL) - Findings\n\n### 1. What Is MachineOSConfig?\n\nMachineOSConfig is the entrypoint CRD for **On-Cluster Layering (OCL)** in MCO. It lets cluster administrators define a custom OS image build — specified via an embedded Containerfile — that the MCO builds on-cluster using Kubernetes Jobs and rolls out to nodes in a target MachineConfigPool.\n\nKey characteristics:\n- API group: `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1`\n- Cluster-scoped (not namespaced)\n- **1:1 relationship with MachineConfigPool** — name must match the pool name (enforced by a CEL validation rule)\n- Status: TechPreview (requires `TechPreviewNoUpgrade` feature gate)\n\nType definition: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types_machineosconfig.go`\n\nCRD manifest: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/zz_generated.crd-manifests/0000_80_machine-config_01_machineosconfigs.crd.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### 2. MachineOSConfig Spec Fields\n\nAll fields from `MachineOSConfigSpec`:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `machineConfigPool.name` | string | Required | Name of the MachineConfigPool to build for and roll out to |\n| `imageBuilder.imageBuilderType` | enum | Required | Build backend. Only valid value: `Job` |\n| `renderedImagePushSecret.name` | string | Required | Secret (in `openshift-machine-config-operator` namespace) with write access to the image registry |\n| `renderedImagePushSpec` | string | Required | Image push destination, e.g. `registry.svc:5000/ns/repo:tag`. Format: `host[:port][/namespace]/name:<tag>` |\n| `baseImagePullSecret.name` | string | Optional | Secret to pull the base OS image. Defaults to cluster-wide pull secret |\n| `containerFile` | `[]MachineOSContainerfile` | Optional | Embedded Containerfile(s). List indexed by arch, max 4 items |\n\n`MachineOSContainerfile` fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `containerfileArch` | enum | Optional | Target arch: `ARM64`, `AMD64`, `PPC64LE`, `S390X`, `NoArch` (default `NoArch`) |\n| `content` | string | Required | Containerfile content. Max 4096 characters. Must contain `FROM configs AS final` |\n\nMachineOSConfig status fields of interest:\n- `status.currentImagePullSpec` — digested image pullspec after a successful build\n- `status.machineOSBuild` — reference to the associated MachineOSBuild object\n- `status.conditions` — state conditions for the build process\n\nSpecial annotation for install-time OCL:\n- `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/pre-built-image` — used to seed a pre-built image digest at install time (defined in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/build/constants/constants.go`)\n\n---\n\n### 3. How On-Cluster Layering Works\n\nArchitecture decision: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/decisions/adr-001-on-cluster-layering.md`\n\nFlow:\n1. Admin creates a MachineConfigPool for the target set of nodes\n2. Admin creates a MachineOSConfig referencing that pool, with a Containerfile and image push destination\n3. Build Controller (`pkg/controller/build/`) watches MachineOSConfig and creates a **MachineOSBuild** object\n4. Build Controller creates a Kubernetes Job that runs `podman build` / `buildah` with the Containerfile\n5. The MCO-generated Containerfile wraps the user's `FROM configs AS final` stage; it first bakes in the rendered MachineConfig (Ignition config) into the base OS image, then runs the user's stage on top\n6. The built image is pushed to `renderedImagePushSpec`\n7. Node Controller detects the successful build, rolls the image out to nodes via drain/reboot (rpm-ostree/bootc rebase)\n\nThe `machine-os-builder` binary (`cmd/machine-config-osimagestream`) is deployed as a Deployment and orchestrates the build lifecycle.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Example YAML Configurations\n\n#### Minimal working MachineOSConfig (v1, current API)\n\nFrom `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineosconfig.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineOSConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: layered-worker\n  annotations:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/pre-built-image: \"quay.io/example/layered-rhcos:latest@sha256:abcd1234...\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigPool:\n    name: layered-worker\n  imageBuilder:\n    imageBuilderType: Job\n  baseImagePullSecret:\n    name: pull-secret\n  renderedImagePushSecret:\n    name: push-secret\n  renderedImagePushSpec: quay.io/example/layered-rhcos:latest\n  containerFile:\n  - containerfileArch: NoArch\n    content: |\n      FROM configs AS final\n      RUN rpm-ostree install httpd && \\\n        ostree container commit\n```\n\n#### Template form (from test fixtures)\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-os-config.yaml` — uses an OpenShift Template with parameters for `NAME`, `POOL`, `IMAGEBUILDERTYPE`, `BASEIMAGEPULLSECRET`, `RENDEREDIMAGEPUSHSECRET`, `PUSHSPEC`, and `CONTAINERFILE`.\n\n#### No base image pull secret variant\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-os-config-nobaseimagepull.yaml` — same as above but omits `baseImagePullSecret`, relying on the cluster-wide pull secret.\n\n#### Go code example (from devex tooling)\n\nFrom `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/machineosconfigs.go`:\n\n```go\n&mcfgv1.MachineOSConfig{\n    Spec: mcfgv1.MachineOSConfigSpec{\n        MachineConfigPool: mcfgv1.MachineConfigPoolReference{Name: poolName},\n        BaseImagePullSecret: &mcfgv1.ImageSecretObjectReference{Name: pullSecretName},\n        RenderedImagePushSecret: mcfgv1.ImageSecretObjectReference{Name: pushSecretName},\n        RenderedImagePushSpec: mcfgv1.ImageTagFormat(finalImagePullspec),\n        ImageBuilder: mcfgv1.MachineOSImageBuilder{ImageBuilderType: mcfgv1.JobBuilder},\n        Containerfile: []mcfgv1.MachineOSContainerfile{{\n            ContainerfileArch: mcfgv1.NoArch,\n            Content: containerfileContents,\n        }},\n    },\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Containerfile Rules\n\nThe Containerfile is embedded in the spec. Key rules (from the quickstart and CRD docs):\n\n- Must include `FROM configs AS final` as the final build stage. The `configs` image is automatically provided by the build system — it contains the base RHCOS image with the rendered MachineConfig already applied.\n- Must call `ostree container commit` at the end of the final RUN statement.\n- Multiple stages are allowed before the `final` stage.\n- If pulling from a private registry inside the Containerfile, those credentials must be in `baseImagePullSecret`.\n- Max content length: **4096 characters**.\n- One entry per architecture, up to 4 total.\n\nExample with `rpm-ostree install`:\n```dockerfile\nFROM configs AS final\nRUN rpm-ostree install tree && \\\n    ostree container commit\n```\n\nExample with RHEL entitlements (removing entitlement repo to avoid later failures):\n```dockerfile\nFROM configs AS final\nRUN rpm-ostree install libreswan && \\\n    rpm-ostree cleanup -m && \\\n    ostree container commit && rm /etc/yum.repos.d/redhat.repo\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Prerequisite Setup Steps\n\nFrom `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/onclusterlayering-quickstart.md` and the devex README:\n\n1. Enable the `TechPreviewNoUpgrade` feature gate (or use `onclustertesting --enable-feature-gate`)\n2. Clone the cluster-wide pull secret into the MCO namespace:\n   ```bash\n   oc create secret docker-registry global-pull-secret-copy \\\n     --namespace openshift-machine-config-operator \\\n     --from-file=.dockerconfigjson=<(oc get secret/pull-secret -n openshift-config -o go-template='{{index .data \".dockerconfigjson\" | base64decode}}')\n   ```\n3. Create (or identify) a push secret with write access to the target registry in the MCO namespace\n4. Create the target MachineConfigPool\n5. (Optional) Create an internal ImageStream:\n   ```bash\n   oc create imagestream os-images -n openshift-machine-config-operator\n   ```\n6. Create the MachineOSConfig\n\nAfter creation, MCO starts `machine-os-builder`, which creates the `MachineOSBuild` and kicks off the Job. After the build, opt nodes into the pool with `oc label node/<node> node-role.kubernetes.io/<pool>=`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Developer Tool for Testing OCL\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/README.md` describes the `onclustertesting` binary with subcommands:\n\n- `onclustertesting setup in-cluster-registry --enable-feature-gate --pool=layered` — full automated setup using an internal ImageStream\n- `onclustertesting setup --pool=<name> --push-secret-name=<s> --final-pullspec=<spec>` — setup with an external registry\n- `onclustertesting setup ci` — CI mode: sets up both control-plane and worker pools and waits for builds and rollout\n- `onclustertesting teardown` — cleans up all OCL objects created by the tool\n- `onclustertesting optin --pool=<pool> --node=<node>` — moves a node into the layered pool\n- Pass `--containerfile-path` to inject a custom Containerfile at setup time\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key Source Files Reference\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types_machineosconfig.go` | Go type definitions for MachineOSConfig, MachineOSContainerfile, ContainerfileArch, ImageTagFormat, etc. |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/zz_generated.crd-manifests/0000_80_machine-config_01_machineosconfigs.crd.yaml` | Full CRD schema with all field validations |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/onclusterlayering-quickstart.md` | End-to-end user quickstart with `oc` commands and YAML examples |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/onclusterlayering-troubleshooting.md` | Troubleshooting guide, recovery steps, known limitations |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/decisions/adr-001-on-cluster-layering.md` | Architecture decision record |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/domain/crds.md` | CRD domain model summary |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineosconfig.yaml` | Concrete YAML example with httpd install |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-os-config.yaml` | OpenShift Template form |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/machineosconfigs.go` | Go helper for creating MachineOSConfig programmatically |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/README.md` | Developer tool usage documentation |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/build/constants/constants.go` | Annotation key constants (pre-built-image, Seeded condition) |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/build/fixtures/objects.go` | Test fixture construction helpers |"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e75a21bc-7faa-413c-8450-02eaf032edac","uuid":"c24ad32b-debb-497f-bd2e-31356eba4a75","timestamp":"2026-06-22T21:09:32.127Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search for documentation and code about MachineOSConfig and on-cluster layering in /home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator. I need to understand:\n1. What MachineOSConfig is and how it's structured (CRD fields, spec)\n2. How to configure on-cluster layering to build custom OS images with additional packages\n3. Any example YAML configs or usage examples\n\nSearch in: docs/, README files, ai-docs/, MCO_DEVELOPMENT.md, MCO_TESTING.md, AGENTS.md, and any relevant Go files or test files that show usage examples. Be thorough — look for example configs, type definitions, and documentation.","agentId":"a1070550a207b5ed7","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a comprehensive picture of MachineOSConfig and on-cluster layering from across the repo. Here is the full report.\n\n---\n\n## MachineOSConfig and On-Cluster Layering (OCL) - Findings\n\n### 1. What Is MachineOSConfig?\n\nMachineOSConfig is the entrypoint CRD for **On-Cluster Layering (OCL)** in MCO. It lets cluster administrators define a custom OS image build — specified via an embedded Containerfile — that the MCO builds on-cluster using Kubernetes Jobs and rolls out to nodes in a target MachineConfigPool.\n\nKey characteristics:\n- API group: `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1`\n- Cluster-scoped (not namespaced)\n- **1:1 relationship with MachineConfigPool** — name must match the pool name (enforced by a CEL validation rule)\n- Status: TechPreview (requires `TechPreviewNoUpgrade` feature gate)\n\nType definition: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types_machineosconfig.go`\n\nCRD manifest: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/zz_generated.crd-manifests/0000_80_machine-config_01_machineosconfigs.crd.yaml`\n\n---\n\n### 2. MachineOSConfig Spec Fields\n\nAll fields from `MachineOSConfigSpec`:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `machineConfigPool.name` | string | Required | Name of the MachineConfigPool to build for and roll out to |\n| `imageBuilder.imageBuilderType` | enum | Required | Build backend. Only valid value: `Job` |\n| `renderedImagePushSecret.name` | string | Required | Secret (in `openshift-machine-config-operator` namespace) with write access to the image registry |\n| `renderedImagePushSpec` | string | Required | Image push destination, e.g. `registry.svc:5000/ns/repo:tag`. Format: `host[:port][/namespace]/name:<tag>` |\n| `baseImagePullSecret.name` | string | Optional | Secret to pull the base OS image. Defaults to cluster-wide pull secret |\n| `containerFile` | `[]MachineOSContainerfile` | Optional | Embedded Containerfile(s). List indexed by arch, max 4 items |\n\n`MachineOSContainerfile` fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `containerfileArch` | enum | Optional | Target arch: `ARM64`, `AMD64`, `PPC64LE`, `S390X`, `NoArch` (default `NoArch`) |\n| `content` | string | Required | Containerfile content. Max 4096 characters. Must contain `FROM configs AS final` |\n\nMachineOSConfig status fields of interest:\n- `status.currentImagePullSpec` — digested image pullspec after a successful build\n- `status.machineOSBuild` — reference to the associated MachineOSBuild object\n- `status.conditions` — state conditions for the build process\n\nSpecial annotation for install-time OCL:\n- `machineconfiguration.openshift.io/pre-built-image` — used to seed a pre-built image digest at install time (defined in `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/build/constants/constants.go`)\n\n---\n\n### 3. How On-Cluster Layering Works\n\nArchitecture decision: `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/decisions/adr-001-on-cluster-layering.md`\n\nFlow:\n1. Admin creates a MachineConfigPool for the target set of nodes\n2. Admin creates a MachineOSConfig referencing that pool, with a Containerfile and image push destination\n3. Build Controller (`pkg/controller/build/`) watches MachineOSConfig and creates a **MachineOSBuild** object\n4. Build Controller creates a Kubernetes Job that runs `podman build` / `buildah` with the Containerfile\n5. The MCO-generated Containerfile wraps the user's `FROM configs AS final` stage; it first bakes in the rendered MachineConfig (Ignition config) into the base OS image, then runs the user's stage on top\n6. The built image is pushed to `renderedImagePushSpec`\n7. Node Controller detects the successful build, rolls the image out to nodes via drain/reboot (rpm-ostree/bootc rebase)\n\nThe `machine-os-builder` binary (`cmd/machine-config-osimagestream`) is deployed as a Deployment and orchestrates the build lifecycle.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Example YAML Configurations\n\n#### Minimal working MachineOSConfig (v1, current API)\n\nFrom `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineosconfig.yaml`:\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineOSConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: layered-worker\n  annotations:\n    machineconfiguration.openshift.io/pre-built-image: \"quay.io/example/layered-rhcos:latest@sha256:abcd1234...\"\nspec:\n  machineConfigPool:\n    name: layered-worker\n  imageBuilder:\n    imageBuilderType: Job\n  baseImagePullSecret:\n    name: pull-secret\n  renderedImagePushSecret:\n    name: push-secret\n  renderedImagePushSpec: quay.io/example/layered-rhcos:latest\n  containerFile:\n  - containerfileArch: NoArch\n    content: |\n      FROM configs AS final\n      RUN rpm-ostree install httpd && \\\n        ostree container commit\n```\n\n#### Template form (from test fixtures)\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-os-config.yaml` — uses an OpenShift Template with parameters for `NAME`, `POOL`, `IMAGEBUILDERTYPE`, `BASEIMAGEPULLSECRET`, `RENDEREDIMAGEPUSHSECRET`, `PUSHSPEC`, and `CONTAINERFILE`.\n\n#### No base image pull secret variant\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-os-config-nobaseimagepull.yaml` — same as above but omits `baseImagePullSecret`, relying on the cluster-wide pull secret.\n\n#### Go code example (from devex tooling)\n\nFrom `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/machineosconfigs.go`:\n\n```go\n&mcfgv1.MachineOSConfig{\n    Spec: mcfgv1.MachineOSConfigSpec{\n        MachineConfigPool: mcfgv1.MachineConfigPoolReference{Name: poolName},\n        BaseImagePullSecret: &mcfgv1.ImageSecretObjectReference{Name: pullSecretName},\n        RenderedImagePushSecret: mcfgv1.ImageSecretObjectReference{Name: pushSecretName},\n        RenderedImagePushSpec: mcfgv1.ImageTagFormat(finalImagePullspec),\n        ImageBuilder: mcfgv1.MachineOSImageBuilder{ImageBuilderType: mcfgv1.JobBuilder},\n        Containerfile: []mcfgv1.MachineOSContainerfile{{\n            ContainerfileArch: mcfgv1.NoArch,\n            Content: containerfileContents,\n        }},\n    },\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Containerfile Rules\n\nThe Containerfile is embedded in the spec. Key rules (from the quickstart and CRD docs):\n\n- Must include `FROM configs AS final` as the final build stage. The `configs` image is automatically provided by the build system — it contains the base RHCOS image with the rendered MachineConfig already applied.\n- Must call `ostree container commit` at the end of the final RUN statement.\n- Multiple stages are allowed before the `final` stage.\n- If pulling from a private registry inside the Containerfile, those credentials must be in `baseImagePullSecret`.\n- Max content length: **4096 characters**.\n- One entry per architecture, up to 4 total.\n\nExample with `rpm-ostree install`:\n```dockerfile\nFROM configs AS final\nRUN rpm-ostree install tree && \\\n    ostree container commit\n```\n\nExample with RHEL entitlements (removing entitlement repo to avoid later failures):\n```dockerfile\nFROM configs AS final\nRUN rpm-ostree install libreswan && \\\n    rpm-ostree cleanup -m && \\\n    ostree container commit && rm /etc/yum.repos.d/redhat.repo\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Prerequisite Setup Steps\n\nFrom `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/onclusterlayering-quickstart.md` and the devex README:\n\n1. Enable the `TechPreviewNoUpgrade` feature gate (or use `onclustertesting --enable-feature-gate`)\n2. Clone the cluster-wide pull secret into the MCO namespace:\n   ```bash\n   oc create secret docker-registry global-pull-secret-copy \\\n     --namespace openshift-machine-config-operator \\\n     --from-file=.dockerconfigjson=<(oc get secret/pull-secret -n openshift-config -o go-template='{{index .data \".dockerconfigjson\" | base64decode}}')\n   ```\n3. Create (or identify) a push secret with write access to the target registry in the MCO namespace\n4. Create the target MachineConfigPool\n5. (Optional) Create an internal ImageStream:\n   ```bash\n   oc create imagestream os-images -n openshift-machine-config-operator\n   ```\n6. Create the MachineOSConfig\n\nAfter creation, MCO starts `machine-os-builder`, which creates the `MachineOSBuild` and kicks off the Job. After the build, opt nodes into the pool with `oc label node/<node> node-role.kubernetes.io/<pool>=`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Developer Tool for Testing OCL\n\n`/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/README.md` describes the `onclustertesting` binary with subcommands:\n\n- `onclustertesting setup in-cluster-registry --enable-feature-gate --pool=layered` — full automated setup using an internal ImageStream\n- `onclustertesting setup --pool=<name> --push-secret-name=<s> --final-pullspec=<spec>` — setup with an external registry\n- `onclustertesting setup ci` — CI mode: sets up both control-plane and worker pools and waits for builds and rollout\n- `onclustertesting teardown` — cleans up all OCL objects created by the tool\n- `onclustertesting optin --pool=<pool> --node=<node>` — moves a node into the layered pool\n- Pass `--containerfile-path` to inject a custom Containerfile at setup time\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key Source Files Reference\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types_machineosconfig.go` | Go type definitions for MachineOSConfig, MachineOSContainerfile, ContainerfileArch, ImageTagFormat, etc. |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/zz_generated.crd-manifests/0000_80_machine-config_01_machineosconfigs.crd.yaml` | Full CRD schema with all field validations |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/onclusterlayering-quickstart.md` | End-to-end user quickstart with `oc` commands and YAML examples |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/docs/onclusterlayering-troubleshooting.md` | Troubleshooting guide, recovery steps, known limitations |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/decisions/adr-001-on-cluster-layering.md` | Architecture decision record |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/ai-docs/domain/crds.md` | CRD domain model summary |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/bootstrap/testdata/bootstrap/layered-worker.machineosconfig.yaml` | Concrete YAML example with httpd install |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/test/extended-priv/testdata/files/generic-machine-os-config.yaml` | OpenShift Template form |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/machineosconfigs.go` | Go helper for creating MachineOSConfig programmatically |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/devex/cmd/onclustertesting/README.md` | Developer tool usage documentation |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/build/constants/constants.go` | Annotation key constants (pre-built-image, Seeded condition) |\n| `/home/jsuri/random-testing/prashanth-help/machine-config-operator/pkg/controller/build/fixtures/objects.go` | Test fixture construction helpers |"}],"resolvedModel":"claude-sonnet-4-6","totalDurationMs":131189,"totalTokens":76012,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2078,"cache_read_input_tokens":70360,"output_tokens":3573,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2078},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":21,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":15,"editFileCount":0,"linesAdded":0,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}}}
