{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01XUC7bhvgAFJsecJFnRMs7b", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Here's how to configure on-cluster layering with `MachineOSConfig`:\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n**1. Enable the TechPreview feature gate** (OCL is TechPreview):\n```bash\noc patch featuregate cluster --type=merge \\\n  --patch='{\"spec\":{\"featureSet\":\"TechPreviewNoUpgrade\"}}'\n```\n\n**2. Create a MachineConfigPool** for your layered nodes:\n```bash\noc create -f - <<EOF\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineConfigPool\nmetadata:\n  name: my-layered-pool\nspec:\n  machineConfigSelector:\n    matchExpressions:\n      - key: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/role\n        operator: In\n        values: [worker, my-layered-pool]\n  nodeSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      node-role.kubernetes.io/my-layered-pool: \"\"\nEOF\n```\n\n**3. Set up secrets** in the `openshift-machine-config-operator` namespace:\n\nCopy the cluster pull secret (for pulling the base OS image):\n```bash\noc create secret docker-registry global-pull-secret-copy \\\n  --namespace openshift-machine-config-operator \\\n  --from-file=.dockerconfigjson=<(oc get secret/pull-secret -n openshift-config \\\n    -o go-template='{{index .data \".dockerconfigjson\" | base64decode}}')\n```\n\nCreate a push secret with write access to your image registry:\n```bash\noc create secret docker-registry my-push-secret \\\n  --namespace openshift-machine-config-operator \\\n  --docker-server=quay.io \\\n  --docker-username=<user> \\\n  --docker-password=<token>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Create the MachineOSConfig\n\nThe `metadata.name` **must match** the MachineConfigPool name exactly (CEL-enforced):\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: machineconfiguration.openshift.io/v1\nkind: MachineOSConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: my-layered-pool\nspec:\n  machineConfigPool:\n    name: my-layered-pool\n  imageBuilder:\n    imageBuilderType: Job          # only valid value\n  baseImagePullSecret:\n    name: global-pull-secret-copy  # in openshift-machine-config-operator ns\n  renderedImagePushSecret:\n    name: my-push-secret           # in openshift-machine-config-operator ns\n  renderedImagePushSpec: quay.io/myorg/my-layered-rhcos:latest\n  containerFile:\n    - containerfileArch: NoArch    # or AMD64, ARM64, PPC64LE, S390X\n      content: |\n        FROM configs AS final\n        RUN rpm-ostree install tree httpd && \\\n            ostree container commit\n```\n\n**Critical Containerfile rules:**\n- Must include `FROM configs AS final` \u2014 `configs` is the MCO-managed base image with your rendered MachineConfig already baked in\n- Must end with `ostree container commit` inside the final `RUN`\n- Max 4096 characters per containerfile entry\n\n---\n\n## What happens next\n\n1. MCO creates a `MachineOSBuild` object and launches a Kubernetes Job that runs `podman build`\n2. The built image is pushed to `renderedImagePushSpec`\n3. Opt nodes into the pool by labeling them:\n   ```bash\n   oc label node/<node-name> node-role.kubernetes.io/my-layered-pool=\n   ```\n4. MCO drains and reboots each node, rebasing onto the new custom image\n\n## Monitor the build\n\n```bash\noc get machineosbuild                          # watch build status\noc get machineosconfig my-layered-pool -o yaml # check .status.currentImagePullSpec\noc logs -n openshift-machine-config-operator \\\n  -l app=machine-os-builder --follow           # build logs\n```\n\n---\n\n**Key source files for deeper reading:**\n- `docs/onclusterlayering-quickstart.md` \u2014 end-to-end walkthrough with `oc` commands\n- `docs/onclusterlayering-troubleshooting.md` \u2014 recovery steps and known limitations\n- `vendor/github.com/openshift/api/machineconfiguration/v1/types_machineosconfig.go` \u2014 full type definitions\n- `devex/cmd/onclustertesting/README.md` \u2014 developer tool for automated OCL setup/teardown"}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 3987, "cache_read_input_tokens": 33850, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 3987, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 7}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "e75a21bc-7faa-413c-8450-02eaf032edac", "uuid": "47413737-2d62-422d-b71a-5fd2fb0a374e", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcJyzdycpEwT9EpuPWGan", "timestamp": "2026-06-22T21:09:51.869Z"}
